<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>ViewCoach | Luthando Mbuyane</title>
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <meta name="description" content="ViewCoach, a live Django interview preparation platform built by Luthando Mbuyane.">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="../assets/css/style.css">
</head>
<body>
<nav class="nav"><div class="nav-container"><a href="../index.html" class="logo">Luthando Mbuyane</a><div class="nav-links"><a href="../index.html">Home</a><a class="active" href="index.html">Projects</a><a href="../about/index.html">About</a><a href="https://github.com/nonluthando" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub</a><a href="../assets/files/Luthando_Mbuyane_JuniorSWE.pdf" download>CV</a></div></div></nav>
<main class="container">
  <section class="project-hero">
    <div class="project-hero-main"><p class="eyebrow">Live Product</p><h1>ViewCoach</h1><p class="hero-role">A structured interview-preparation platform for creating, importing and practising technical, behavioural and repository-debugging material.</p><p class="hero-description">ViewCoach is designed around a larger product question: “Given the interview I have coming up, what should I practise now?” The live version establishes the production foundation and question library needed before planning and AI features are added.</p><div class="buttons"><a class="btn primary" href="https://viewcoach.onrender.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Open Live App</a><a class="btn" href="https://github.com/nonluthando/ViewCoach" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">View Repository</a></div></div>
    <div class="project-hero-side"><h3>Implemented Stack</h3><div class="fact-list"><p><strong>Core:</strong> Django 5.2 modular monolith</p><p><strong>Data:</strong> PostgreSQL in local, test and production environments</p><p><strong>Quality:</strong> pytest, Ruff and GitHub Actions</p><p><strong>Deployment:</strong> Render</p></div></div>
  </section>

  <section><div class="card"><h3>The Product Decision</h3><p>Most interview-preparation tools help users store material. ViewCoach starts from a different problem: preparation already requires a lot of decisions, and choosing what to study each day adds more friction before the work begins.</p><p>The current live version focuses on structured material and reliable workflows. Spaced repetition, review scheduling, the Focus Engine, goals and AI are intentionally not claimed as implemented yet.</p></div></section>

  <section><div class="section-header"><h2>What Is Live</h2><p>The deployed product currently contains Milestones 0, 1 and 1.1.</p></div><div class="grid two">
    <div class="project-card"><h3>Production Foundation</h3><p class="muted">Custom email-based users, registration, login, logout, protected dashboard, PostgreSQL environments, a database-aware health endpoint, CI and production settings.</p></div>
    <div class="project-card"><h3>Structured Question Library</h3><p class="muted">Technical, behavioural and repository-debugging question types with type-specific create, edit and detail experiences.</p></div>
    <div class="project-card"><h3>Private Study Workflows</h3><p class="muted">User-owned libraries, authorization rules, search and filters, progressive technical reveals, debugging diagnosis reveals and dashboard summaries.</p></div>
    <div class="project-card"><h3>Bulk Import and Review</h3><p class="muted">Imports from pasted text, TXT, Markdown, CSV, DOCX and text-based PDFs, with resumable review batches, duplicate detection, editable titles, type overrides and transactional creation.</p></div>
  </div></section>

  <section><div class="section-header"><h2>Architecture Decisions</h2><p>The architecture is intentionally simple enough to understand and strong enough to grow.</p></div><div class="grid two">
    <div class="project-card"><h3>Modular Monolith</h3><p class="muted">Django apps provide domain boundaries without introducing distributed-system complexity the project does not need.</p></div>
    <div class="project-card"><h3>PostgreSQL From the Start</h3><p class="muted">Local, test and production environments use PostgreSQL so development behaviour matches production more closely.</p></div>
    <div class="project-card"><h3>Typed Question Models</h3><p class="muted">A concrete base question with typed child models allows each interview format to store the information it actually needs.</p></div>
    <div class="project-card"><h3>Deterministic Before AI</h3><p class="muted">Structured product logic remains separate from future AI behaviour so planning and progress can stay inspectable and testable.</p></div>
  </div></section>

  <section><div class="section-header"><h2>Next Milestones</h2><p>These are future features, not part of the current live claim.</p></div><div class="grid two">
    <div class="project-card"><h3>Practice and Review History</h3><p class="muted">Practice records, self-assessment, mistakes, confidence and review history.</p></div>
    <div class="project-card"><h3>Focus Engine</h3><p class="muted">Deterministic recommendations based on interview context, curriculum coverage, weak areas, available time and previous reviews.</p></div>
    <div class="project-card"><h3>Goals and Scheduling</h3><p class="muted">Interview goals, target dates, availability and readiness evidence.</p></div>
    <div class="project-card"><h3>Grounded AI Support</h3><p class="muted">Later retrieval and explanation features with citations, evaluation and safe fallbacks.</p></div>
  </div></section>
  <section class="center"><a class="btn" href="index.html">Back to Projects</a></section>
</main>
<footer class="footer"><div class="container footer-content"><p>© 2026 Luthando Mbuyane</p><p class="muted">South Africa · Open to relocation</p></div></footer>
</body>
</html>
